-- J-Power to Spend $1.2 Billion to Replace Two Hiroshima Plants, Nikkei Says
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-08-02T17:14:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/j-power-to-spend-1-2-billion-to-replace-two-hiroshima-plants-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             Electric Power Development Co., also
known as J-Power, will spend more than 100 billion yen ($1.2
billion) to build a new power plant to replace two older plants
in Hiroshima Prefecture, Nikkei English News reported, citing
the company.  
          
          


  


        